'''Heritage Jail Museum''' also known as '''Jail Museum''' and '''Sangareddy District Jail<ref>{{cite news|title=Sangareddy District Jail, India: The prison tourists pay to enter and spend the night|url=http://www.traveller.com.au/sangareddy-district-jail-the-prison-tourists-pay-to-enter-and-spend-the-night-gre2bf|publisher=Traveller.com.au|date=September 12, 2016}}</ref>''' is a 220-year-old colonial-era jail, now converted into a museum. It is located in [[Sangareddy]], [[Sangareddy district]] of Indian state [[Telangana]]. The jail allows tourists to live a prisoner's life for 24 hours at a price of Rs.500 ($A9.90).<ref>{{cite news|title=Feel the jail programme sees good response|url=https://telanganatoday.com/feel-the-jail-programme-sees-good-response|publisher=[[Telangana Today]]|date=July 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pay Rs 500 and spend a day at Sangareddy jail in Telangana|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/pay-rs-500-and-spend-a-day-at-sangareddy-jail-in-telangana/story-eLK4rTUwg26CPLfwtgxN9K.html|publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=August 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Feel like a ‘prisoner’ for a day at this Telangana jail museum|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/feel-like-a-prisoner-for-a-day-at-this-telangana-jail-museum/|publisher=[[Indian Express]]|date=September 1, 2016}}</ref> The museum displays the paintings and other artifacts related to crime and prison life in India.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Apparasu|first1=Srinivasa Rao|title=Prison tourism: How it feels to spend a day in this 220-year-old Telangana jail|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/escape-boredom-by-spending-a-day-in-this-220-year-old-telangana-jail-for-rs-500/story-jpdn5agPjsUU5iMNHDKE6J.html|publisher=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=September 6, 2016}}</ref>

== History ==
According to the PWD Records, this imprison was built during the Prime Ministership of [[Salar Jung I]] in 1796 A.D., during [[Nizam]] rule in the [[Hyderabad State|princely state of Hyderabad]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Heritage Jail Museum, Sangareddy|url=http://www.telanganatourism.gov.in/partials/destinations/heritage-spots/sangareddy/sangareddy-jail.html|website=telanganatourism.gov.in|publisher=[[Telangana State Tourism Development Corporation]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=First jail museum inaugurated in Medak|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/First-jail-museum-inaugurated-in-Medak/article14387463.ece|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|date=June 6, 2016}}</ref> It was closed in 2012. 

==Museum==
In June 2016, the jail was converted into a museum by prison department, when M. Lakshmi Narasimha, the Deputy SP of the jail came up with the ''Feel The Jail'' idea.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Duttagupta|first1=Samonway|title=A jail in Telangana is letting tourists live a prisoner's life for 24 hours at a price of Rs 500|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/telangana-tourism-sangareddy-jail-travel-india-aguada-cellular-andaman-lifetr/1/755241.html|publisher=[[India Today]]|date=September 2, 2016}}</ref>

